race.comment: Tough. TIPSY TORONADO (8) has switched from a Darwin yard on a 22-day return. She's been plainer her last two, but the form prior reads well for this contest. In an in-form stable and will carry a feather with the 4kg claimer engaged. A winnable assignment and the betting will be key. DELUSIONALDICTATOR (2) resumes and performs on the fresh side. Has to skip over from a wide gate but gets in well with the 3kg claim and can feature with average luck. The lightly raced OUR SQUAMOSA (7) won her Maiden at a short quote and then was expected to deliver again in a CL2, but faded out after chasing the speed. She's much better than that and maps for the run of the race. TANGO STEPZ (3) is hard to catch, but the well-performed veteran cannot be underestimated. She's been freshened and is likely to race well.
